'''Crowne Plaza Times Square''' is a 795-room hotel situated in the [[Times Square]] area of [[New York City]]'s [[midtown Manhattan]], located at 1601 [[Broadway (Manhattan)|Broadway]],<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://commercialobserver.com/2018/05/vornado-refis-times-square-crowne-plaza-with-250m-loan/|title=Vornado Refis Times Square Crowne Plaza With $250M Loan|date=2018-05-09|work=Commercial Observer|access-date=2018-09-06|language=en-US}}</ref> between W48th and W49th Streets.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.emporis.com/buildings/115392/crowne-plaza-hotel-new-york-city-ny-usa|title=Crowne Plaza Hotel, New York City {{!}} 115392 {{!}} EMPORIS|last=GmbH|first=Emporis|website=www.emporis.com|access-date=2018-09-06}}</ref> At 480 feet (146 meters),<ref name=":1" /> with 46 floors,<ref name=":0" /> it is the [[List of tallest hotels in the world|94th tallest hotel in the world]], the 29th tallest hotel in the [[United States]], and the 15th-tallest hotel in New York City. The hotel was designed by The Alan Lapidus Group, completed in 1989<ref name=":0" /> and opened in 1990.
The hotel is a mixed-use skyscraper with the 795-key Crowne Plaza hotel, 7,700 square feet of retail space, 197,000 square feet of office space, and a 159-space parking garage. New York's largest conference center, the [[American Management Association|American Management Association']]<nowiki/>s Executive Conference Center, is on the sixth through eighth floors with a total of 88,066 square feet. [[Learning Tree International]] has 25,000 square feet; the [[Town Sports International Holdings|New York Sports Club]] has 28,418 square feet; and the [[The Hershey Company|Hershey Company]] has 7,000 square feet of retail space on street level.<ref name=":0" />
The hotel is the [[flagship]] of the [[Crowne Plaza]] brand. In 2008, the hotel underwent an $85 million renovation which revamped the lobby, restaurant and bar areas, as well as updated all of the guest rooms and the hotel's more than {{convert|23000|sqft|m2}} of function space. Amenities include the following: one of the largest hotel-based fitness facilities in the city, the [[New York Sports Club]] located on the 15th floor; the Broadway 49 Bar & Lounge overlooking Broadway; Brasserie 1605 with views of the 24/7 Times Square light show; two business centers; concierge; room service; and on-site valet parking. The Crowne Plaza Times Square is pet-friendly for quadrupeds up to 25 pounds.
In April, 2018 [[Vornado Realty Trust]] refinanced the hotel with a $250 million loan from [[Deutsche Bank]] and [[Morgan Stanley]].<ref name=":0" />
