{{Infobox ice hockey player | name = Libor Zábranský | image = Libor zabransky 2017.jpg | caption = | image_size = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1973|11|25}} | birth_place = [[Brno]], [[Czechoslovakia]] | league = [[National Hockey League|NHL]], [[American Hockey League|AHL]], [[Czech Extraliga|ELH]] | team = | former_teams = | position = [[Defenceman]] | ntl_team = CZE | height_ft = | height_in = | weight_lb = | shoots = | career_start = 1991 | career_end = 2004 }} '''Libor "Zábrda" Zábranský''' (born November 25, 1973 in [[Brno]], [[Czechoslovakia]]) is a retired professional [[ice hockey|hockey]] player and current coach.
==Playing career== Zábranský was drafted 209th overall in the 9th round of the [[1995 NHL Entry Draft]] by the [[St. Louis Blues]]. Zábranský played the majority of his career in the Czech Republic but he did play 40 games over two seasons with St. Louis in the [[National Hockey League|NHL]]. After retiring from playing due to health problems at the age 30, he became majority owner of the Czech Extraliga team [[Kometa Brno|HC Kometa Brno]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hc-kometa.cz/clanek.asp?id=356 |title='Chci pomoci Kometě do extraligy, léta tam patřila a patří tam, říká Libor Zábranský' |last= |first= |coauthors= |date=2005-07-13 |work= |publisher= |language=Czech}}</ref>
