{{Infobox person
| name = Syed Manzur Elahi
| image = 
| native_name = সৈয়দ মঞ্জুর এলাহী
| native_name_lang = bn
| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1942|02|26|df=y}}
| birth_place = [[Calcutta]], [[British India]]
| nationality = Bangladeshi
| education = [[University of Dhaka]]
}}

'''Syed Manzur Elahi''' is a prominent businessperson in [[Bangladesh]].  He is the chairman of [[Apex group]], a leading business organisation in Bangladesh.  He is also the founding chairman of Mutual Trust Bank and Grey Advertising Bangladesh.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mutualtrustbank.com/about_bod_bio_detail.php?pid=about_bod_manzur_elahi |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-01-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130630111257/http://www.mutualtrustbank.com/about_bod_bio_detail.php?pid=about_bod_manzur_elahi |archivedate=30 June 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

==Career highlights==
Manzur joined the erstwhile Pakistan Tobacco after completing [[Master of Arts|M.A.]] in [[Economics]] from the [[University of Dhaka]].  Prior to that, he received his [[B.A]] from [[St. Xavier's College, Calcutta]]. He left the lucrative job to start his own tannery business. In 1996, he was appointed as an advisor to the non-partisan Caretaker Government of Bangladesh.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=244995|title=Open new avenues for jobs|date=2012-08-05|website=The Daily Star|access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref>

